//FAQs??

-How many squares do I need for a baby blanket?

This can vary, it really can be however big or small you like, but i generally do 4x4 or 5x5.

This blog post might be useful: http://bit.ly/1UIobie

-How many chains shall I do for a *single/double/etc' blanket?

Again, this can vary. I would suggest that you do your chain and lay it down agains the bed you are wanting it for. It should be the same width. You should then ad a few more to make it a little wider.

This blog post might be useful: http://bit.ly/1UIobie

-How much yarn do I need?

Unfortunately, I will be able to answer individuals questions about how much yarn you would used do to multiple factors affecting it. Such as, your tension, the size of hook and the yarn being used.

I am a Full Time content creator for my Blog and YouTube.

title: 4inch pompom using folded paper
description:
Have a hard time making pompom? Try this. Make a fluffy 4 inch pompom without a pompom maker. I used folded paper instead. Learn how to tie the pompom very tight so that it wont fall apart. I wrap the folded paper gently 130 times using 2 strands of medium 4 weight yarn 100% acrylic(It's redheart super saver). Remember, "The more wraps, the fluffier pompom". 
Note: Put glue into both knots to make it secured( I forgot it when I was making the video). You can also save all those cut offs for stuffing.

If the video is too slow: click the video settings or the 3 dots(if youre using phone. It's in the right corner of the video) & set to your desired playback speed.

Thank you so much for watching and subscribing, for giving a thumbs up and sharing my videos. It means a lot to me and it keeps me motivated to make more videos of my projects. Thank you. Have a beautiful day!!!

title: How I Usually Make Pom Pom For Hat
description:
Yarn pom pom making at home without a pom pom maker. This is I usually make my pom pom for crocheted hat. I'm using folded paper. Take two strands of yarn & wrap the folded paper 70 to 80 times. I did this method to avoid pompom from falling apart easy.

If the video is too slow: click the video settings or the 3 dots(if you're using phone. It's in the right corner of the video) & set to your desired playback speed.

title: Crochet Ribbed Hat
description:
Super easy and fun to make! Perfect for anyone in the family! This is a great first project if you are just learning to crochet.
I am dedicating this project to the Grade 7 "Fashion and Design Class" that I will help to learn how to crochet.
To the next generation of crocheters!

Written Instructions:
1 Skein - Any Yarn-150 Metres or more, 
 Main colour of Hat
 (I am using Bernat Premium, Medium #4)
1 Skein - Any Yarn - Pom Pom
1 Crochet Hook - 5 mm (6 mm if using a chunky yarn)
Darning Needle
Scissors
Measuring Tape

Abbreviations:
Ch = Chain
Hdc = Half Double Crochet
St = Stitch
Ss = Slip Stitch

Instructions:
Chain 12â€-14â€ or 30-36 cm (or longer for a slouchy hat)

Row 1 - Hdc in 3rd ch from hook, Hdc in each ch across.
           - Ch 1 and turn

Row 2 - *Working in back loops only, Hdc in first st, and in each st all the way across. Ch 1, turn.*
             (Be very careful not to miss the last stitch, and that you have the same amount in             every row).
 
Repeat Row 2 until you have reached approximately 17â€-20â€ or 44-50 cm
 (Or until it fits around your head).

Stop at an EVEN amount of rows.

Fold in half

Insert hook into Hdc then into ch space, Ss into each stitch across.

Leave about 20â€ or 50 cm. Cut yarn and pull through.

With Darning Needle, weave in and out to gather top of hat. Pull snug and tie to beginning yarn. Leave this tail of yarn to tie Pom Pom to.

Make Pom Pom, Attach to hat.
To add trim, just put one row of Single Crochet around the edge. ğŸ˜ƒ

title: Easy Crochet Winter Ribbed Hat
description:
Hello and welcome to Rich Textures Crochet!

Today we are going to learn how to crochet the Easy Winter Beanie.  This hat was designed in collaboration with @SugarBushYarns (https://www.sugarbushyarns.com) for Operation Gratitude (https://www.lovecrafts.com/en-us/c/article/operation-gratitude)

This hat is easy to crochet and versatile in its design.  You will find the free written crochet pattern here: https://richtexturescrochet.com/2019/08/30/easy-winter-beanie-free-crochet-pattern/

Buy the yarn here (affil): http://www.tkqlhce.com/click-9216139-13759646?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yarnspirations.com%2Fsugar-bush-bold-yarn--spruce-grove%2F6480033029.html&cjsku=6480033029

Skill Level: Easy

Gauge: 18 sts x 9 rows of pattern = 4 inches.

Finished Size: Approximately 9.5 x 13 inches laid flat, 20-21 inch circumference at hat opening.

Yarn: Bold by Sugar Bush Yarns (100% extra fine super wash merino wool; 3.5 oz/100g; 190 yds/174 m); 2 Skeins Doverâ€™s Sand

Hook: Size J/10 (6.0 mm). Adjust hook size if necessary to obtain correct gauge.

Notions: Yarn Needle, pompom if desired.

Thank you for watching!

Please don't forget to subscribe to my YouTube Channel: https://www.youtube.com/c/RichTexturesCrochet/ and share this video and give it a thumbs up if you enjoyed it! I will be updating this channel weekly!

You can find free crochet patterns on my blog: https://richtexturescrochet.com

You can follow Rich Textures Crochet on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/RichTextures/


Find me on IG here: https://www.instagram.com/RichTexturesCrochet/

Thanks again for stopping by! Be sure to crochet something beautiful today!

Sarah

title: Easy Children's Crochet Hat Pattern
description:
Hello and welcome to Rich Textures Crochet!

Today we are going to learn how to crochet an easy children's winter hat! This hat pattern in a variation of the Easy Winter Ribbed Hat found here on my channel: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k0WgJLkheCY&t=1s

The yarn in this tutorial can be purchased here (Affil): http://www.kqzyfj.com/click-9216139-13759646?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yarnspirations.com%2Fca-en%2Fsugar-bush-bold-yarn--atlantic-almond%2F6480033005.html&cjsku=6480033005

The written pattern can be found here on my blog: https://richtexturescrochet.com

Skill Level: Easy

Gauge: 21 sts x 22 rows of pattern = 4 inches.

Finished Size (Note that the hat has quite a bit of stretch and length accounts for length of brim which will be turned up when worn): 
Premie: 5 inches in length, 4.5 inches laid flat (will fit head measurement 13 inches) 
0-3 Months: 6 inches in length, 5 inches across laid flat (will fit head measurement 14 inches) 
3-6 Months: 7 inches in length, 5.5 inches across laid flat (will fit head measurement 15 inches) 6-12 Months: 8 inches in length, 6 inches across laid flat (will fit head measurement 17 inches) 12-24 Months: 9 inches in length, 6.5 inches across laid flat (fits head measurement 18 inches) 
Child: 10 inches in length, 7 inches across laid flat (will fit head measurement 20 inches)

Yarn: Bold by Sugar Bush Yarns (100% extra fine super wash merino wool; 3.5 oz/100g; 190 yds/174 m); 1 skein Doverâ€™s Sand for the premie-24 month size; 2 Skeins Doverâ€™s Sand for the child size

Hook: Size I/9 (5.5 mm). Adjust hook size if necessary to obtain correct gauge.

Notions: Yarn Needle

Thank you for watching!

Please don't forget to subscribe to my YouTube Channel: https://www.youtube.com/c/RichTexturesCrochet/ and share this video and give it a thumbs up if you enjoyed it! I will be updating this channel weekly!

You can find free crochet patterns on my blog: https://richtexturescrochet.com

You can follow Rich Textures Crochet on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/RichTextures/

Find me on IG here: https://www.instagram.com/RichTexturesCrochet/

Interested in purchasing my crochet patterns in PDF format? You may do so in my Etsy Shop (https://www.etsy.com/ca/shop/RichTexturesCrochet) or on Ravelry (https://www.ravelry.com/designers/rich-textures-crochet)

Thanks again for stopping by! Be sure to crochet something beautiful today!

Sarah

title: HOW to CROCHET an EASY WINTER HAT - Simple Textured Beanie by Naztazia
description:
You can learn how to Crochet an Easy Winter Hat in this DIY tutorial video. Hi I'm Donna Wolfe from Naztazia. This is a nice simple textured hat that works great for beginners. The crunch stitch, which is easy to crochet, adds a nice texture to the top part of this beanie hat. And the single crochet ribbing adds a good amount of stretch to the hat.

This video shows a woman's size hat, but my written pattern shows child, teen, women, and men sizes as well. To make this hat, you will need to know how to make a chain, slip stitch, single crochet, and half double crochet. I'm using  Red Heart Heat Wave yarn, which is a lovely acrylic worsted weight yarn with heat generating properties. And I'm using a size H 5 mm hook. I'm also using an optional pompom for the top of the hat.

title: How to CROCHET STAR STITCH HAT - Easy Winter Hat by Naztazia
description:
You can learn how to Crochet a Star Stitch Hat in this video tutorial. Hi I'm Donna Wolfe from Naztazia. Hereâ€™s a lovely textured winter hat. The entire work is constructed using the side-to-side method. Both the folded-over ribbing and the top section crown are made at the same time. One end of the work contains the half double crochet ribbing while the other end contains the star stitch. The ribbing looks like a knitted ribbing due to alternating the front and back loops of the HDCs. A faux fur pompom is sewn on top for decoration.

Once you see how the star stitch hat is made you will find itâ€™s a relatively simple beanie pattern. For this hat, other basic crochet terms you will need to know are the chain (CH) and half double crochet (HDC). It is also helpful to know that the anatomy of the half double crochet stitch contains 3 loops. There is a back loop, a front loop, and a front-front loop, also known as the third loop. If this loop appears in the back some people call it a back bump. Additionally, the stitch itself has 3 vertical loops. Thereâ€™s a longer one on one side, and two shorter ones on the other side. Weâ€™ll be using almost all of these different loops in this head warmer!

Iâ€™m also using a size H 5 mm crochet hook for this pattern. Plus I really love the Red Heart Heat Wave yarn. I chose the gray color called Passport for this design. The heat wave yarn, when exposed to ultraviolet sunlight, keeps you 12 degrees warmer. Iâ€™m not sure exactly how it works; however the photo was taken in 28 degrees F weather here in freezing cold Pennsylvania, and I was nice and toasty warm!

title: Crochet Small Flower with Puff Stitch
description:

Yarn used: Medium 4 weight 100% Acrylic
Crochet hook: 4.25mm

Abbreviations used:
Ch - Chain
Sp - Space
St - Stitch

My videos have written instructions only, no voice. You can write the whole instructions from my videos for personal use only. 

Thank you for adding my tutorials link when you share/post your finished projects from my tutorials to other social. I really appreciate it. Happy Crocheting!!!

title: How to crochet Easy Ribbed Beanie / Hat Style 1
description:
You don't have to be able to read a pattern to make this beanie. In this video I will teach you how to make this beautiful ribbed stitch beanie.  Using the crochet rib stitch gives this beanie a knitted look. If you can't knit, this is a great alternative. Use this stitch and crochet this beanie. Below are suggested hook sizes.  Remember everyone crochets a little differently.

SUBSCRIBE and never miss a video:   
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC2vNl4iUpM4Z1Lxlg2BN_4Q?sub_confirmation=1

Infant- Size G Hook, Babies  Size H  hook, Toddler Size I hook.  To crochet a beanie for an older child use a size J hook and a medium weight worsted yarn. For adults you can use a size K hook and a heavier weight of yarn (maybe even a chunky weight. The pattern is the same for all sizes. Only the size of hook and weight of yarn changes. This makes this the perfect beanie pattern for all sizes. From Baby - adult size. Follow the same pattern.. Happy crocheting

title: Crochet Chain of Hearts | Scrap Yarns Project Idea
description:
Crochet chain of hearts easy. Idea for keychain, bookmark, an embellishment/trim to something or as a gift tie, could be a bracelet, garland and more. Project idea for scrap yarns. Easy and Step by step crochet tutorial.

Picot guide: Chain 1, insert hook into the top of last Single crochet through side loop & pull through.

Tips: When the work gets curl, just stretch all the stitches out.

Skill level: Beginner to easy

If the video is too fast or slow: click the video settings or the 3 dots & set to your desired playback speed.

Yarn used: Medium 4 weight yarn 97% cotton & 3 % metallic polyester.(I love this cotton spark)
(the read heart is made with 100% acrylic).
Crochet hook :4.25mm

Abbreviations:
Ch - chain
SC - single crochet
Dc - double crochet
St - stitch

My videos have written instructions only, no voice. You can write the whole instructions from my videos for personal use. 
 Happy Crocheting!!!
Thank you so much for watching and subscribing, for giving a thumbs up and sharing my videos. It means a lot to me. Have a beautiful day!!!
Lyza Walters

THE WALKERS waren eine niederlÃ¤ndische Country-Rock- und Popgruppe der 1970er Jahre.

Biografie
Die Band ging 1963 aus einer Formation namens The Mosam Skiffle Group hervor und spielte Popmusik mit Skiffle-Akzent, die durch die etwas spÃ¤ter zur Gruppe gekommene SÃ¤ngerin Jean Innemee geprÃ¤gt wurde. Die Single Thereâ€™s No More Corn on the Brasos war der erste Charterfolg und erreichte im Februar 1971 Platz 4 in den Niederlanden. Vier Monate spÃ¤ter folgte mit My Darling Helena! ein weiterer Hit auf Platz 4 der heimatlichen Hitparade. Der dritte Top-10-Hit, Taboo, schaffte es im August 1972 in den Niederlanden auf Platz 8 und stieg im Oktober auf Platz 38 der deutschen Charts.

Als 1973 RenÃ© Innemee zu The Walkers stieÃŸ, Ã¤nderte die Gruppe ihren musikalischen Stil in Richtung Country, blieb aber weiterhin erfolgreich. Dance of Love erreichte im August 1973 Platz 10, Oh, Lonesome Me im Januar 1974 Platz 12 und Jack of Diamond im Mai Platz 21 der hollÃ¤ndischen Charts.

Im Jahr 1977 gehÃ¶rten The Walkers neben The Classics und Rainbow zu den ersten PreistrÃ¤gern bei Limburgs Vastelaovesleedjes Konkoer, einem jÃ¤hrlichen Wettstreit um das beste Karnevalslied. A banda, originalmente, consistiu dos estudantes Roger Waters, Nick Mason, Richard Wright e Syd Barrett. O nome Pink Floyd Ã© a abreviaÃ§Ã£o de The Pink Floyd Sound, nome sugerido por Barrett em homenagem a dois mÃºsicos de blues admirados por ele: Pink Anderson e Floyd Council.
O guitarrista e vocalista David Gilmour juntou-se Ã  banda em 1968, meses antes da saÃ­da de Barrett do grupo, devido ao seu estado de deterioraÃ§Ã£o mental, agravado pelo uso de drogas. Dois Ã¡lbuns foram lanÃ§ados apÃ³s esse conflito: A Momentary Lapse of Reason e The Division Bell. ApÃ³s quase duas dÃ©cadas de amargor entre seus membros, o Pink Floyd se reuniu em 2005 para uma Ãºnica apresentaÃ§Ã£o, no concerto para a caridade Live 8. Wright morreu em 2008. title: Crochet Beanie Hat
description:
How to crochet a Crochet Beanie Hat. Advanced Easy Level. Written Pattern below. Copyright Â© Crochet Hooks You. All Rights Reserved.

Crochet Beanie Hat Written Pattern:

Materials Required
1 skein/ball of Red Heart Fiesta Yarn, Color: Buff. You will get 2-3 Crochet Beanie Hats from 1 skein/ball.
6.0mm Crochet Hook
Craft Scissors
Yarn Needle

Skill Level
Advanced Easy

Size
Teenager to Adult Ladies Size

Stitches & Terms
This pattern is using U.S. stitches and terms.
BPdc = Back Post double crochet
ch = chain
ch-3 = 3 chain stitches previously made
dc = double crochet
post = the middle section or length of a stitch
rep = repeat
rnd = round
sl st = slip stitch
st/s = stitch/es

Notes: ch 3 = 1 dc st

Making the Crown (top of beanie)

ch 5, sl st into 1st ch to form a ring.

Rnd 1: ch 3, (working over yarn tail) 15 dc into ring, sl st into top of ch-3. (16 sts)

Rnd 2: ch 3, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into next st, rep from * around to last st, 2 dc into last st, sl st into top of ch-3. (24 sts)

Rnd 3: ch 3, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 2 sts, rep from * around to the last 2 sts, 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into next st, sl st into top of ch-3. (32 sts)

Rnd 4: ch 3, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 3 sts, rep from * around to the last 3 sts, 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 2 sts, sl st into top of ch-3. (40 sts)

Rnd 5: ch 3, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 4 sts, rep from * around to the last 4 sts, 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of the next 3 sts, sl st into top of ch-3. (48 sts)

Rnd 6: ch 3, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 5 sts, rep from * around to the last 5 sts, 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of the next 4 sts, sl st into top of ch-3. (56 sts)

Making the Sides
Rnds 7 to 17: ch 3, 1 BPdc around post of each dc st around to the end, sl st into top of ch-3.

Making the Edge
Rnd 18: 1 sl st into each st around to the end.

Finish off and weave in yarn tails with a yarn needle.

title: Crochet messy bun hat subtitles only The same hat English video below description box
description:
The same hat with ENGLISH https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yMUeGAb3HAs

How to crochet Messy bun hat. Aran / worsted weight yarn. 
K/6.5mm crochet hook.

Crochet messy bun hat keep you warm and looking good.

Messy bun hat protect your head from the cold. 

Messy bun hat size for this tutorial -  21"/53cm. Stretchy fit up to 23" head  circumference.

Standard adult size 21"-23" (53cm-58.4cm)

Ch 15
Start 3rd chain from hook. Double crochet  in each stitch, Ch 2, turn.

Right side : FPdc 3, BP dc 2, FPdc 2, BPdc 2, FPdc 3, dc in ch 2 space, ch 2, turn. 
Wrong side: BPdc 3, FP dc 2, BPdc 2, FPdc 2, BPdc, 3, dc in ch 2 space, ch 2 turn , this need repeat for headband. 44 rows all together.

For headband strap: ch 15, Start 3rd chain from hook. Double crochet  in each stitch, Ch 2, turn.
Right side : FPdc 3, BP dc 2, FPdc 2, BPdc 2, FPdc 3, dc in ch 2 space, ch 2, turn. 
Wrong side: BPdc 3, FP dc 2, BPdc 2, FPdc 2, BPdc, 3, dc in ch 2 space, ch 2 turn ,  
Right side : FPdc 3, BP dc 2, FPdc 2, BPdc 2, FPdc 3, dc in ch 2 space.

Headband join together with slip stitch. Sew strap ends together. Knot is ready. 

Find middle of the headband strap there is 4 stitches. Skip 2 first stitches and start count 22 stitches left side, 23rd stitch will be first stitch now to start crochet top of the hat. 

join yarn, Ch 1, double crochet in each ch 2 space or row. Strap place pick up 4 sts. 
next 4 rounds, Ch 2,  (FP double crochet and dc) repeat all around, join with slip stitch. 
next round: repeat dc2tog all around. Fasten off.

NEEDLES

In this crochet tutorial I will walk you step-by-step and show you how to make this super easy super bulky crochet beanie.

All supplies needed and written instructions are show below.  

ADDITIONAL SIZES ARE AVAILABLE IN WRITTEN PATTERNhttps://www.etsy.com/ca/listing/545492686/super-bulky-crochet-hat-pattern-for?ref=shop_home_active_6

CROCHET STITCHES USED
ch â€“ chain
sc â€“ single crochet
sk â€“ skip 
st â€“ stitch
sts â€“ stitches
sl st â€“ slip stitch
rpt - repeat

MATERIALS 
9.0 mm hook
10 mm hook
Buttons (optional)
Tapestry Needle
Stitch Markers
Pompom if desired
170g / 97m Super Bulky Yarn 

Adult 19.5â€ X 7.5â€ 

*Hat is worked in continuous rounds. Do not join. Use a stitch marker at the beginning of round for easier counting

Using 10 mm hook ch 2 

Rnd 1: Work 6 sc in 2nd st from hook. (6)

Rnd 2: 2 sc in 1st st and each st around (12)

Rnd 3: 1 sc in 1st st *2 sc in next st, 1 sc in next st* rpt from * to * till end of rnd (18)

Rnd 4: 1 sc in 1st 2 sts *2 sc in next st, 1 sc in next 2 sts* rpt from * to * till end of rnd (24)

Rnd 5: 1 sc in 1st 3 sts *2 sc in next st, 1 sc in next 3 sts* rpt from * to * till end of rnd (30) 

Rnd 6: 1 sc in 1st 4 sts *2 sc in next st, 1 sc in next 4 sts* rpt from * to * till end of rnd (36)

Rnd 7: 1 sc in 1st 11 sts *2 sc in next st, 1 sc in next 11 sts* rpt from * to * till end of rnd (39)

Rnds 8-15: Sc in 1st st and each st around. (39)

Change to 9.00 mm hook and continue below

Rnds 16-18: Sc in 1st st and each st around. (39)

Fasten off and weave in ends

Gauge: 20 sts x 31 rows of pattern = 4 inches.

Finished Size: Approximately 8 x 9 inches laid flat, 20-21 inch circumference when stretched.

Yarn: Rapture by Sugar Bush Yarns (50% merino/50% Llama Soft; 3.5 oz/100g; 211 yds/193 m); For Hat with Brim: 1.5 Skeins Smoky Spirit; For Hat with no brim: 1 Skein Smoky Spirit - This is a light weight yarn.

Hook: Size J/10 (6.0 mm). Adjust hook size if necessary to obtain correct gauge.

Notions: Yarn NeedleThank you for watching!

title: Crochet CHY Ribbed Hat
description:
How to crochet the Crochet CHY Ribbed Hat. Easy Level. Written Pattern below. Copyright Â© Crochet Hooks You. All Rights Reserved.

CHY Ribbed Crochet Hat Written Instructions:

Materials Required:
2 balls of Red Heart With Love Holly Berry Yarn (medium worsted weight, category 4)

10mm Crochet Hook

Yarn Needle

Craft Scissors

Head Circumference: 21 inches/54 cms
Notes: ch 2 = 1 dc st. When joining into ch-2, sl st into both loops of the 2nd ch st.

Using 2 balls of yarn together - ch 4, sl st into 1st ch to form a ring.

Rnd 1: ch 2, (working over yarn tail as you go) 13 dc into ring, sl st into top of ch-2 to join. (14 sts)

Rnd 2: ch 2, 1 FPdc around ch-2 under join, [1 dc into next st, 1 FPdc around the same dc] 13 times, sl st into top of ch-2 to join. (28 sts)

Rnd 3: ch 2, 1 FPdc around ch-2 under join, 1 FPdc around next FPdc, [1 dc between next 2 sts, 1 FPdc around each of the next 2 sts] 13 times, sl st into top of ch-2 to join. (42 sts)

With a yarn needle sew center yarn tail in and around the inside of Rnd 1.

Rnd 4: ch 2, sk the ch-2, 1 FPdc around each st to the end, sl st into top of ch-2 to join. (you will continue to have 42 sts for the remainder of the pattern.)

Rnds 5 to 15: Rep Rnd 4.

If you want the hat longer then repeat round 4 as many times as you need to.

Finish off.

Sew yarn tail in with a yarn needle.

Turn up the last round to create the brim.

title: Crochet Beanie for Beginners - Adult Sizes
description:
How to crochet a Crochet Beanie for Beginners. Beginner level. Written Pattern below.
Copyright Â© Crochet Hooks You. All Rights Reserved.


Crochet Beanie for Beginners Written Pattern:

Materials Required

1 skein/ball of Red Heart With Love Lilac Yarn

6.5mm Crochet Hook

Craft Scissors

Yarn Needle

Skill Level
Beginner

Size/Head Measurements
Ladies - 22 inches/56 cms or Mens 24 inches/62 cms

To make smaller sizes - leave the last round or a few of the last rounds off from the crown part of the pattern and leave off a round or a few rounds off from the sides.

To make the mens size - add the extra increase round in after Round 6 which is stated below.

Stitches and Terms

This pattern is using U.S. stitches and terms.

ch = chain

ch-2 = 2 chain stitches previously made

dc = double crochet

hk = hook

rep = repeat

rnd/s = round/s

sl st = slip stitch

sp = space

st/s = stitch/es

Note: ch 2 = 1 dc st right throughout this pattern.

Making the Crown (top of beanie)

Using Lilac Yarn, ch 5, sl st into 1st ch to form a ring.

Rnd 1: ch 2, (working over yarn tail) 15 dc into ring, sl st into top of ch-2. (16 sts)

Rnd 2: ch 2, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into next st, rep from * around to last st, 2 dc into last st, sl st into top of ch-2. (24 sts)

Rnd 3: ch 2, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 2 sts, rep from * around to the last 2 sts, 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into next st, sl st into top of ch-2. (32 sts)

Rnd 4: ch 2, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 3 sts, rep from * around to the last 3 sts, 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 2 sts, sl st into top of ch-2. (40 sts)

Rnd 5: ch 2, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 4 sts, rep from * around to the last 4 sts, 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of the next 3 sts, sl st into top of ch-2. (48 sts)

Rnd 6: ch 2, * 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of next 5 sts, rep from * around to the last 5 sts, 2 dc into next st, 1 dc into each of the next 4 sts, sl st into top of ch-2. (56 sts)

If you want a larger crown for a mens beanie add in this following increase round before starting the sides:

ch 2, * 2 dc into the next st, 1 dc into each of the next 6 sts, rep from * around to the last 6 sts, 2 dc into the next st, 1 dc into each of the next 5 sts, sl st into top of ch-2. (64 sts)

Sides

Rnds 7 to 14: ch 2, 1 dc into each st around to the end, sl st into top of ch-2.

Finish off.

Sew yarn tails in with a yarn needle.


More Crochet Video Tutorials at
http://www.youtube.com/user/crochethooksyou

http://youtu.be/-4dxlQuuXpA

Lyrics:
Well, I heard there was a secret chord
that David played and it pleased the Lord
but you don't really care for music, do you?
Well it goes like this:
the fourth, the fifth, the minor fall and the major lift
the baffled king composing Hallelujah

Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah

Well your faith was strong but you needed proof
you saw her bathing on the roof
her beauty and the moonlight overthrew ya
She tied you to her kitchen chair
she broke your throne and she cut your hair
and from your lips she drew the Hallelujah.

Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah

Well, baby, I've been here before
I've seen this room and I've walked this floor, you know
I used to live alone before I knew ya
And I've seen your flag on the marble arch
and love is not a victory march
it's a cold and it's a broken Hallelujah.

Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah.

Well, there was a time when you let me know
what's really going on below
but now you never show that to me, do ya?
But remember when I moved in you
and the holy dove was moving too
and every breath we drew was Hallelujah.

Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah

Maybe there's a God above
but all I've ever learned from love
was how to shoot somebody who outdrew ya
And it's not a cry that you hear at night
it's not somebody who's seen the light
it's a cold and it's a broken Hallelujah.

Hallelujah, hallelujah, hallelujah, hallelujah...

title: Santa Esmeralda - Don't Let Me Be Misunderstood (1977) â€¢ TopPop
description:
Santa Esmeralda starring Leroy Gomez
Santa Esmeralda is an American-French-Spanish disco group formed in the 1970s; perhaps best known for their hit disco remakes of the 1960s hits "Don't Let Me Be Misunderstood" and "House of the Rising Sun". The group featured original lead singer Leroy GÃ³mez in 1977-1978 and singer Jimmy Goings from late 1978 until 1983, and once again original lead singer Leroy GÃ³mez from the 1990s to this day.

"Santa Esmeralda" was formed in 1977 by French producers Nicolas Skorsky and Jean Manuel de Scarano, singer-songwriters who had launched their own label with the aim of producing artists who would record their compositions. Upon meeting singer Leroy GÃ³mez in Paris, the duo recruited him for the group's first record, "Don't Let Me Be Misunderstood", which debuted on the independent French label, Fauves Puma. A sudden success in Europe, the record was picked up for worldwide distribution by Casablanca Records. 
Originally written in 1964 for Nina Simone, her version had failed to chart, and the song was picked up by rock group The Animals the following year. The essential nature of the song is Latin and flamenco, which combined with that urgency lent itself to the disco sensibility in the 1970s. The song became a hit all over again, first topping the U.S. Disco chart and then matching the #15 peak of The Animals' version on the Billboard Hot 100. 
It reached #5 in the Dutch Top 40 on 17 September 1977.
The music is composed by Bennie Benjamin, Jean De Scarano, Gloria Caldwell, Nicolas Sharsky, Raymond Donnez, Sol Markus.

The song was featured in a famous sword fight scene by Uma Thurman in Quentin Tarantino's film 'Kill Bill' from 2003.

This Toppop recording was made on 20 August 1977.

TopPop was the first regular dedicated pop music TV show in the Dutch language area. Dutch broadcaster AVRO aired the programme weekly, from 1970 to 1988. Presenter Ad Visser hosted the show for its first fifteen years.

title: LAMBADA
description:
A song from the movie - Lambada

"Lambada", also known as "Chorando Se Foi (Lambada)" or "Llorando se fue (Lambada)", is a song recorded by French pop group Kaoma. It features guest vocals by Brazilian vocalist Loalwa Braz. It was released as the first single from Kaoma's debut album Worldbeat. The video, filmed on Cocos beach in the city of Trancoso, in the state of Bahia, Brazil, features the Brazilian child duo Chico & Roberta.

The song in Portuguese is a mix cover of MÃ¡rcia Ferreira's 1986 hit "Chorando se foi" (lyrics translated to Portuguese) and the Cuarteto Continental hit "Llorando se fue" (first upbeat version of the song introducing the accordion), released in 1984 through the Peruvian record label INFOPESA and produced by Alberto Maravi;[1][2] both songs were adapted from the 1981 Bolivian song Llorando se fue by Los Kjarkas.

At the time of release, the song has been regarded as the most successful European single in the history of CBS records with sales of 1.8 million copies in France and more than 4 million across Europe. It has sold more than 12 million copies worldwide, making it one of the world's most-famous singles of all time[3]

title: Easy Crochet Mock Cable Hat
description:
Introducing the Mock Cable Hat for women. It's a really neat concept as it's uses the Jacobs Ladder Concept for the brim. There is two Jacobs Ladders that slink around the outside of the brim. For me, just making that element makes me giggle with excitement.

The buttons are for decorative reasons but act as a hiding spot for where the jacobs ladder starts and finishes. So it's an element of necessity but hidden by decorative buttons.

Get the free pattern at http://bit.ly/2jkBJCD #BernatDazzle #crochet #learntocrochet #crochettutorial .

title: Crochet Small Heart Applique Easy
description:
Crochet easy heart applique. Beginner crochet heart tutorial. Great for diy headband, hair clips, crocheted hats, keychain and more. 

Picot guide: Chain 1, insert hook into the top of last SC made through side loop & pull through.
 
Tip: When the stitches get curl, just stretch out all the stitches.

If the video is too fast or slow: click the video settings or the 3 dots & set to your desired playback speed.

Skill level: Beginner

Yarn used in the video: Medium 4 weight yarn, 97% cotton & 3% Metallic polyester. (The other hearts shown in the video is made with leftover yarn Medium 4 100% acrylic & 100% cotton).

Crochet hook: 4.25mm

title: Lobo - I'd Love You To Want Me â€¢ TopPop
description:
Kent LaVoie (born July 31, 1943), better known by his stage name Lobo, is an American singer-songwriter who was successful in the early 1970s, scoring several U.S. Top 10 hits including "Me and You and a Dog Named Boo", "I'd Love You to Want Me", and "Don't Expect Me to Be Your Friend". These three songs, along with â€œWhere Were You When I Was Falling In Loveâ€, gave Lobo four chart toppers on the Easy Listening/Hot Adult Contemporary chart.

"I'd Love You to Want Me" is the title of a popular song from 1972 by Lobo (the stage name of Roland Kent LaVoie). He wrote the song, which appears on his album 'Of A Simple Man'.

Released as a single in the fall of 1972, "I'd Love You to Want Me" was the singer's highest charting hit on the Billboard Hot 100 chart, where it spent two weeks at No. 2 in November of that year. It was kept from the top spot by Johnny Nash's hit song, "I Can See Clearly Now". The single was the second of four of his songs to hit No. 1 on the Easy Listening chart, where it had a one-week stay at that top spot in December 1972. It became a gold record.

When originally released in the United Kingdom in 1972, the song failed to reach the UK Singles Chart; however, a re-release of the single in 1974, on the UK label, peaked at No. 5.[5]

The song also topped the music charts in at least seven nations, including Australia (Kent Music Report, two weeks), Canada (RPM Magazine, one week), and Germany (Media Control Charts, 13 weeks in 1973-1974).

title: Terry Winter - Our love dream
description:
Thomas William Standen, nasceu em 08 de maio de 1941.  Cantor, compositor. Filho de Maria Thereza Standen e Charles Walter Standen, brasileiro, neto de ingleses. O avÃ´ materno era veterinÃ¡rio, a avÃ³ dona de casa e residiam no Brasil. A famÃ­lia de seu pai firmou-se na cidade de Penedo, subdistrito de Resende (RJ) onde passou grande parte de sua infÃ¢ncia.
Seu pai tinha uma pequena fÃ¡brica e a famÃ­lia tinha uma fazenda em Penedo. Todos estudaram em colÃ©gio inglÃªs, e mantinham as tradiÃ§Ãµes e os costumes ingleses, alÃ©m de falarem muito bem o portuguÃªs e inglÃªs.

Surgiu na jovem guarda com nome Tommy Standen, com mÃºsicas gravadas por artistas como Nilton Cesar ("Ao Mundo Vou Contar", 1966) e Ronnie Von ("Pequeno PrÃ­ncipe", parceria com Fred Jorge, 1967), paralelamente a seus prÃ³prios discos ("O Quente", RCA, 1966; "A Varanda", RCA, 1967). Em 1972 reinventou-se como Terry Winter, aproveitando a onda de artistas que se faziam passar por estrangeiros; fez grande sucesso interpretando composiÃ§Ãµs prÃ³prias como "You'll Notice Me" e "Summer Holiday" atÃ© se revelar brasileiro no programa de Silvio Santos, anunciando inclusive que mudaria novamente o nome artÃ­stico, para Thomas Williams, mudanÃ§a esta que nÃ£o ocorreu. Winter/Standen deixou de fazer sucesso como intÃ©rprete, mas ainda freqÃ¼entou as paradas graÃ§as a mais uma metamorfose: como Chico Valente, assinou vÃ¡rios sucessos de mÃºsica sertaneja moderna como "Sonho De Um Caminhoneiro", "MÃ£e De Leite" (ambas gravadas por MilionÃ¡rio e JosÃ© Rico), "Convite De Casamento" (gravdas por Athayde e Alexandre), "Meu Velho Amigo" (Tonico e Tinoco) e "Rei do Gado" (tema de abertura da telenovela homÃ´nima da Rede Globo) compostas em parceria com Nil Bernardes, o mesmo Neil Bernard co-autor de "Summer Holiday" e outras.

Faleceu no dia 22 de setembro de 1998, vÃ­tima de pneumonia. Foi sepultado no cemitÃ©rio Campo Grande, no bairro de Interlagos.

title: EL SONIDO DEL SILENCIO. Subtitulada en Ingles-EspaÃ±ol.PAUL SIMON & ART GARFUNKEL
description:

Hay personas que han encontrado un mensaje religioso en la lÃ­rica de esta canciÃ³n pero a mÃ­, lejos del significado literal de algunas de sus palabras me ha sugerido un mensaje de contenido social muy interesante. Veamos.
La canciÃ³n comienza en un "monÃ³logo" entre el intÃ©rprete y la oscuridad, quizÃ¡s sea porque Paul Simon acostumbraba a ir a componer sus canciones al pequeÃ±o cuarto de baÃ±o de su casa. En una entrevista Ã©l nos ha revelado que estando encerrado allÃ­, en la "oscuridad" lograba mÃ¡s imaginaciÃ³n y escuchaba mejor los sonidos de su guitarra, etc.
Por eso creo, que el verdadero tema de la canciÃ³n comienza cuando nos relata que mientras "dormÃ­a", empieza a percibir una importante "visiÃ³n" que llega a Ã©l arrastrÃ¡ndose, escalando suavemente, deduzco, al igual que una planta trepadora, subiendo imperceptiblemente desde sus visiones mÃ¡s simples, hasta llegar al lugar de sus pensamientos mÃ¡s profundos, tal como una gran idea y procurando que algo naciera, deja allÃ­ su semilla pero... entre el "Sonido de el Silencio". Este detalle es muy importante, no lo olviden. "El Sonido del...", como mÃ¡s adelante nos advierten no es nada bueno. Esta expresiÃ³n al igual que: "La Luz de NeÃ³n" son repetidas varias veces en la canciÃ³n asÃ­ que tengo la impresiÃ³n que ambas son utilizadas como claves. 
TambiÃ©n creo que ese "sueÃ±o" es una metÃ¡fora y que se refiere a una "condiciÃ³n", a un estado de adormecimiento o hipnosis colectiva que le impedÃ­a ver y entender claramente la situaciÃ³n dentro de la cual se desarrollaba su vida y la de muchas personas mÃ¡s. 
Aunque la canciÃ³n particularmente no acusa o responsabiliza a nadie por aquella condiciÃ³n, sÃ­ logro percibir detrÃ¡s a "grandes poderes" que muy bien podrÃ­an ser: los poderes polÃ­ticos, los econÃ³micos y o los religiosos controlando el destino y suerte de aquellas personas. Todos tienen intereses muy comunes por eso en la prÃ¡ctica se puede percibir como un â€œpoder Ãºnicoâ€. Hay lugares aun peores, donde todos ellos obedecen al poder militar, como en los paÃ­ses totalitarios comunistas y bajo gobiernos de dictaduras.
Con â€œLa Luz de Neon" se ha querido aludir a: "la propaganda", convertida por ellos en una favorable herramienta para desinformar, persuadir y adoctrinar, utilizando eficazmente los medios masivos de la divulgaciÃ³n pÃºblica, sobre todo a travÃ©s de la T.V. para acondicionar a aquellas personas â€œadormecidas".
-Cuando mis ojos fueron â€œacuchilladosâ€ por el destello de una Luz de NeÃ³n... y tocÃ³ el "Sonido del Silencio"-,  nos dice.
FÃ­jese cÃ³mo la canciÃ³n describe, de quÃ© manera avasalladora penetra y de cÃ³mo ahora ambas expresiones simbÃ³licas actÃºan como "entidades" que se buscan entre sÃ­ dentro de cada persona, puÃ©s de la existencia de la Ãºna, depende la supervivencia de la otra. 
Pero ya la "visiÃ³n" habÃ­a logrado desarrollo dentro de Ã©l como para poder ver a la "Luz de NeÃ³n" al desnudo, sin su capacidad para persuadirle ni engaÃ±arle y fue entonces cuando viÃ³ y comprendiÃ³ muchas cosas que antes ignoraba. 
Nos dice: - En la desnudada "Luz", vÃ­ a diez mil personas... quizÃ¡s mÃ¡s, que hablaban sin hablar y que escuchaban sin oir..., escribiendo canciones nunca compartidasâ€. Estas eran las personas que ya habÃ­an logrado â€œdespertarâ€ pero que todavÃ­a no se atrevÃ­an a perturbar al: "Sonido del Silencio". 
Y aquÃ­ aparece el segundo sÃ­mbolo clave: "El Sonido del Silencio", con lo que se quiere aludir a la â€œcensuraâ€ o tambiÃ©n a su otra forma, la â€œautocensuraâ€, creadas con â€œEl terror de Estadoâ€ con las que se manipula y controla a las personas silenciando su derecho a la libre expresiÃ³n y a la "verdad", fuerza moral con la que se puede llegar a desmentir y revelar pÃºblicamente todas sus oscuras pretensiones.
El â€œSonido del Silencioâ€ sÃ³lo permite un tipo de â€œexpresiÃ³nâ€, aquella que sÃ³lo diga lo que conviene o beneficia a ese Poder. Y si pudiÃ©ramos considerar a esa expresiÃ³n como un sonido, entonces podrÃ­amos decir que en â€œEl Sonido delâ€¦" hay sonido, pero que al mismo tiempo tambiÃ©n hay â€œsilencio", porque no dirÃ¡ nunca nada la verdad, es la demagogia del Poder. Â¿Recuerdas en el principio cuando todavÃ­a aun en medio del "sueÃ±o" la visiÃ³n tuvo que convivir entre "El Sonido del Silencio" Â¿QuÃ© es si nÃ³ dentro deâ€¦ la censura? 
Pero aun asÃ­ quiso hablarles de su "visiÃ³n". Les advirtiÃ³ el peligro del... â€œSilencio": 
-Â¡crece como un cancer!-,
pero sus palabras cayeron en los pozos...(enterradas profundamente, silenciadas), del "Sonido del...â€( la censura).
Ellos prefirieron esclavizarse y seguir adorando aquella "condiciÃ³n", entonces intentÃ³ otra manera, utilizando los mismos medios de "La Luz de NeÃ³n" les orientÃ³ a buscar las palabras de su "vision", escritas furtivamente tal como si fueran verdaderas profecÃ­as, (advertencias), en las paredes de algunos lugares pÃºblicos, (...no censurados) y susurradas como ahora mismo, entre el "Sonido del Silencio".

Bryan Ferry, (born 26 September 1945, Washington, County Durham, UK) is an English singer, musician, and songwriter. Ferry came to public prominence in the early 1970s as lead vocalist and principal songwriter with the band Roxy Music, who enjoyed a highly successful career with three number one albums and ten singles entering the top ten charts in the United Kingdom. "Slave to Love" is the first single released from Roxy Music singer Bryan Ferry's 1985 release, Boys and Girls. The song is one of Ferry's most popular solo hits. 
The single was released on 28 April 1985 and spent 9 weeks in the UK charts in 1985, peaking at number 10. The song features Neil Hubbard and Keith Scott on lead guitar, Dire Straits' Guy Fletcher on keyboards, Omar Hakim on drums, and Tony Levin on bass guitar.

title: The Cars - Drive (Live Aid 1985)
description:
The Cars performing at Live Aid in front of 100,000 people in the John F. Kennedy Stadium, Philadelphia USA on the 13th July, 1985. The event was organised by Sir Bob Geldof and Midge Ure to raise funds for the Ethiopian famine disaster. Broadcast across the world via one of the largest satellite link-ups of all time, the concerts were seen by around 40% of the global population.
Remember to subscribe to stay up to date with all new releases in the channel.

{PurÃª de Batatas}
Cozinhe as batatas e amasse. Adicione o leite, o creme de leite e a manteiga. Mexa bem e tempere com sal e pimenta-do-reino.

Playing For Change (PFC) is a movement created to inspire and connect the world through music, born from the shared belief that music has the power to break down boundaries and overcome distances between people. The primary focus of PFC is to record and film musicians performing in their natural environments and combine their talents and cultural power in innovative videos called Songs Around The World. Creating these videos motivated PFC to form the Playing For Change Bandâ€”a tangible, traveling representation of its mission, featuring musicians met along their journey; and establish the Playing For Change Foundationâ€”a separate 501(c)3 nonprofit organization dedicated to building music and art schools for children around the world. Through these efforts, Playing For Change aims to create hope and inspiration for the future of our planet.

To learn more about the work of the PFC Foundation, visit http://www.playingforchange.org

title: Macrame Sling Bag Diamond Pattern Tutorial
description:
Macrame Sling Bag Diamond Pattern Tutorial 

Hi, Macrame Lovers...

Sudah lama saya tidak membuat tutorial tas macrame. Kebetulan saya mendapatkan pesanan Macrame Sling Bag dengan dua warna,  jadi saya menyempatkan waktu untuk merekam cara pembuatannya agar bisa berbagi dengan anda. Tutorial Macrame Sling Bag yang saya buat kali ini mirip dengan yang pernah saya bagikan sebelumnya di channel youtube saya ini : https://youtu.be/c6kJ8p5wd3w
Bedanya hanya terletak pada design pola pada penutup tas dan bag strapnya saja. Sesuai permintaan customer saya, saya mengaplikasikan Diamond Pattern with Square Knot in the center pada bagian depan tas dan juga pada bag strap.

Material :
1. Tali katun 3mm
     a. Bagian Badan Tas 
         - 1 utas, panjang 300 cm, warna merah (di video saya sebut sebagai tali utama)
        - 16 utas, panjang 360 cm, warna merah
        - 8 utas, panjang 360 cm, warna hitam

    b. Bagian Tali Selempang/Bag Strap
       - 2 utas, panjang 10 meter dan 1 utas, panjang 5 meter

2. 2 pcs Pengait tas, ukuran lebar 2,5 cm 
3. 2 pcs Ring D, ukuran lebar 2,5 cm
4. 1 pasang kancing magnet, ukuran diameter 1,8 cm/2 cm
5. Gunting
6. Jarum Tapestri
7. Lakban

Simpul yang digunakan : Lark's Head Knot, Square Knot, Double Half Hitch Knot dan gathering knot.

Hasil akhir Macrame Sling bag ini berukuran 24 cm x 18 cm dengan panjang bag strap 100 cm.



Find Me On Instagram :
https://www.instagram.com/trini.id/

Bahan yang saya pakai bisa didapatkan disini :
1. Pengait Tas : https://shp.ee/q76prfj
2. Tali katun : https://shp.ee/crrg7bj
3. Ring D ukuran 2,5 cm : https://shp.ee/cenuqxj
4. Kancing Magnet : https://shp.ee/wrn2k6j

Per chi ha piacere di sostenere il nostro canale, abbiamo deciso di usare uno strumento semplice e sicuro per tutti. Grazie di cuore a tutti voi: https://paypal.me/aronegianina

Ciao a tutti, oggi prepariamo insieme una crema al cioccolato super golosa: LA CREMA NAMELAKA. Dalle origini giapponesi, Ã¨ nata da una collaborazione tra dei pasticcieri nipponici e la scuola di Pasticcieria francese Ã‰cole du Chocolat di Valrhona. Ãˆ di una semplicitÃ  unica, si puÃ² fare tranquillamente in 5min, non ha uova, farina, zucchero e non necessita di cottura. Dal giapponese "namelaka" significa "vellutato" o "super cremoso" ed Ã¨ molto versatile e gustosa.

5 g di gelatina

title: Almond, Cacao and Caramel Tart I ì•„ëª¬ë“œ ìºëŸ¬ë©œ ì¹´ì¹´ì˜¤ íƒ€ë¥´íŠ¸ I Glaze Theory I ê¸€ë¼ì‚¬ì£¼ ì´ë¡  I On The Table
description:
Hello!

This time I am going to show you how to make this beautiful and flavorful tart. 

Flavor pairing of almond, caramel, and cacao nibs is well balanced and perfect harmony.

I will explain everything step by step and theory, so please turn on the subtitles!

The videos I make are not just about the recipes. 

I am trying to put all the knowledge I know in the video as much as I can.

So stay tuned for upcoming videos!

Don't forget to hit the subscribe button and set an alert if you haven't done yet!  OR I WILL EAT YOUR PHONE.

I see you guys in the next video!



------------------------------------------------------------------- 

Yield: 6 8 cm-dia Tart


Components

*Cacao Nibs Shortcrust

-Butter    105 g 
-Confectioners' Sugar  90 g 
-Hazelnut Flour 30 g 
-Salt    2.5 g 
-Cocoa Powder (Cacao Barry Extra Brute) 20 g
-Cacao Nibs  20 g
-Eggs    50 g 
-Pastry Flour (T45) 60 g / 150 g 

*Egg Wash
-Egg Yolk 48 g 
-Heavy Cream 12 g

*Brown Sugar Almond Sponge
 
-Butter 53 g
-Confectioners' Sugar 39 g
-Heavy Cream   19 g
-Invert Sugar (Trimoline) or honey 3.5 g
-Egg Yolks   53 g
-Almond Flour   81 g
-Corn Starch   7 g
-Sea Salt    1.4 g
-Egg Whites   84 g
-Brown Sugar   35 g

*Almond Cremeux

-Milk       49 g
-Glucose Syrup    2.5 g
-Gelatin Powder (200 Bloom) 1.3  g
-Water for Gelatin    6.5g
-White Couverture (Cacao Barry Zephyr 34%) 76 g
-Heavy Cream 123 g
-Almond Paste 50%   38 g
-Salt      0.2 g

*Almond Vanilla Praline

-Almonds with Skin  100 g
-Sugar     67 g
-Vanilla Bean    1/2 ea

*Light Dulcey Mousse

-Milk 78 g
-Gelatin Powder (200 Bloom) 3.1 g
-Water for Gelatin    15.5 g
-Dulcey Couverture (Valrhona) 148 g
-Heavy Cream    155 g

*Caramel Glaze 

-Sugar   86 g
-Water  86 g
-Glucose Powder  35 g
-Dextrose   58 g
-Condensed Milk  74 g
-Gelatin Powder (200 Bloom) 6.5 g
-Water for Gelatin  32.5 g
-Cocoa Butter  42 g
-Nappage (Valrhona Absolu Cristal) 86 g
-Gold Dust
-Bronze Dust

*Dulcey Chocolate Decor
*Cocoa Powder
*Cacao Nibs (Ghana)

Recipe

â€¢ Mango puree 

mango 300g 
sugar 100g 
lemon juice 3g

1. Put mango and sugar in a pot and boil.
2. Add a little lemon juice and mix and blend finely with a blender.

â€¢ Glaze 

starch syrup 50g 
sugar 50g 
condensed milk 35g 
water 27g 
melted white chocolate 50g
gelatin sheet 5g 
yellow food coloring

1. Add starch syrup, sugar, condensed milk, and water and bring to a boil.
2. When it starts to boil, remove from heat and add the soaked gelatin sheet, and mix.
3. Add melted white chocolate and food coloring and mix.
4. Ripening in the refrigerator for up to one night
5. When using it, melt it warm in the microwave.

â€¢ Mango jelly

mango puree 80g 
sugar 6g 
warm water 30g 
gelatin sheet 5g

1. Add mango puree and sugar and mix.
2. Add warm water and soaked pan gelatin and mix.
3. Refrigerate in a mousse ring for at least 1 hour

â€¢ Yogurt jelly

plain yogurt 40g 
sugar 15g 
gelatin sheet 5g 
half whipped cream 60g 
vanilla extract

1. Combine yogurt, sugar, and vanilla extract.
2. Add a soaked gelatin sheet and mix (if gelatin doesn't melt well, heat it in the microwave and melt it).
3. Mix the whipped cream and pour it over the mango jelly and refrigerate it.

â€¢ Mango Moose

2 egg yolks 
sugar 25g
hot milk 130g 
vanilla extract
whipped cream 120g 
mango puree 90g 
gelatin sheet 8g

1. Combine yolk, sugar, and vanilla extract and pour in hot milk.
2. Pour all over the pot and heat until thick.
3. Remove from heat, add soaked pan gelatin, mix, and cool.
4. Add half whipped cream and mango puree and mix.
5. Put jelly and mango mousse in the mousse ring and freeze for at least two hours.

â€¢Sponge Sheet

2 egg whites
sugar 50g
2 egg yolks
vanilla extract
cake flour 40g 
milk 15g 
vegetable oil 11g

title: Apa kamu punya jeruk yang asem? bikin ini aja cuma 3 bahan | Orange Candy | Isi Toples Lebaran
description:

200 ml air jeruk (pilih jeruk yang rasanya asam)

title: Honey Hot Tea Bomb! EASY, TASTY, and BEAUTIFUL!
description:
Hello!

So excitied to be back with anothe Hot Tea Bomb, this time with Honey! Hope you all enjoy!

INGREDIENTS: 
1 Cup of Sugar
1/3 Cup Honey
2 Tablespoons of Water

Add ALL ingredients to a pot. Stir with wooden spoon until sugar desolves. Let it cook on medium high heat. Once the sugar starts boiling, check the temperature. The sugar must be at 290* or if you prefer, the hard crack stage on  your candy thermometer. 
Once it reaches the right temperature, remove the pot from heat.
CAREFULLY pour the hot sugar in your molds and swirl around the edges, as you see in the video. Once the mold is coated all around, place the mold in the freezer for about 5 minutes or fridge for 10minutes. 
Remove the sugar spheres from the molds, add tea or tea bags, and seal the sugar spheres with a hot plate as seen in the video. 

Enjoy the beauty and taste of your Honey tea bombs! You deserve it!

I hope you love it! Tag @allthingsohmarie on IG. I'd love to see your creations!

******Below are the links to the materials used*******

https://youtu.be/8DZO5M-bMEc

title: Caramel Mousse Cake. Caramel Mirror Glaze
description:
Hi, this time I willl make a caramel cake with a brownie base and caramel mirror glaze. You can find the recipe below

1. Brownie
100g dark chocolate
30g unsalted butter
1 egg
30g sugar
a pinch of salt
1 tsp vanilla extract (5ml)
30g cake flour (you can use all purpose flour)
1/2 tsp baking powder
bake the cake at 180C for 20 - 22 minutes
about 50ml espresso to moist the cake

2. Salted caramel layer with nuts
30g sugar
1 tbsp water
75ml heavy cream
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
1 gelatine leaf (1.5g), bloomed in cold water for about 10 minutes
25g nuts (roasted and chopped)

3. White chocolate mousse
2 egg yolks
20g sugar
1tsp vanilla
50ml milk
50ml heavy cream
bring it to 80C over small medium heat, stir constantly
5g gelatine leaves (bloomed)
sift the mixture over 30g white chocolate

200ml heavy cream
15g powdered sugar

Freeze the mousse cake for at least 3 hours

4. Caramel mirror glaze
80g sugar
1 tbsp water
80g warm water (or 80ml)
40g condensed milk
80g glucose
3g gelatine leaves (bloomed)
60g white chocolate

Pour the glaze over freezed cold mousse cake, the glaze temperature is 27C. After pouring, put the cake back into the fridge for at least 2 hours to thaw before serving.

5. Coral tuile:  attach them to the cake just before serving or they will become soft quickly
75ml warm water
30ml oil
5g powdered sugar
8g all purpose flour

title: Fluffy Japanese Cheesecake
description:
Japanese Cheesecake (6" inch / 15cm)

INGREDIENTS :
A) 100g cream cheese
     76g milk
     35g unsalted butter

B) 35g All purpose flour

C) 38g egg yolks

D) 78g egg whites 
     40g sugar 

æ—¥å¼èŠå£«è›‹ç³• (6" å¯¸ / 15cm)

ä»½é‡: ä¸€å€‹6å‹è›‹ç³•  
A) 100g å¿Œå»‰èŠå£«
       76g ç‰›å¥¶
       35g ç‰›æ²¹

B) 35g æ™®é€šéºµç²‰

C) 38g è›‹é»ƒ

D) 78g è›‹ç™½
   40g ç´°ç ‚ç³–

INSTRUCTIONS : 
Step 1- Preheat oven 150Â°c. Double boil ingredients (A) Cream cheese, milk, butter in a mixing bowl. Whisk until no lump. Put ingredients (B) All purpose flour, mix well. Last ingredients (C). 

Step 2- Beat egg whites, sugar separate into 3 portions. Egg white must be refrigerated before start beating (more stable when mixing) ; beat into soft peak. 

Step 3- Separate egg whites into 2 portions, fold gently with cheese mixture using a spatula. 

Step 4- Using the baking oil, spray on a 6â€ inch mould on all edges.

Step 5- Pour the mixture into mould. Stir the surface till smoothly with a stick. Prepare a tray then pour hot water around 1 inch height and bake the cheesecake in 150Â°c for a total of 70 minutes. First, bake 20 minutes with door close. Secondly, bake 25 minutes and leave a gap at ovenâ€™s door (around 1.5 cm) to let the hot steam slowly release out. This is to prevent the cake rises too high and the cheesecake surface from cracking. Third, rotate the cake and bake for another 25 minutes leaving a small gap while it bakes until golden brown. Total baking time is 70 minutes.

Important tips.
1. Cake pan must fully cover and spray with baking oil spray (the cake will rise perfectly)
2. Before start mixing,the egg white must refrigerate after separated with egg yolk.
3. Your egg whites need to be soft peak after adding sugar in. 
4. Bake the cake at 150 cÂ° with water bath. First 20 minutes, second 25 minutes(turn over the cake and leave a small gap at oven door) third 25 minutes. Before start the third 25 minutes, your cheesecake surface must starting turn golden brown. If not, you need to rise the temperature to 160Â° for the third 25 minutes.

title: Holiday Party Must-Have: Fast and Delicious Mini Cheesecakes in 30 Minutes
description:
Cheesecake
Ingredients 
for the crust:
60 g softened or melted butter 
2 cups crushed Graham cracker, tea biscuits,Â  digestive cookies or..) 

for the cheesecake:
300 g room temperature creamcheese 
100 g sugar 
2 eggs(room temperature)
1 tbsp flour
1-2 tbsp lemon/lime juice
1 tbsp vanilla
3/4 cup(200g) sour cream (room temperature) 

Topping:
cranberry sauceÂ  and blackberry 

mix melted/softened butter with the crushed cookies 
divide the cookie in 12 cupsÂ  and firmly across the bottom of the cups.
set them aside
beat the cream cheese until softened
add sugar and mix it well until smooth 
add the 2 eggs one at a time and mix well
add 1tsp lemon zest
add the lemon/lime juice and vanilla
add the room temperature sour cream and flour
mix it well until it is smooth 

pour the cheesecake batter in the paper cups(3/4th of the cups)
bake at 325Â°F forÂ  15- 20 minutes 
Important point:
avoid overmixing in all the steps to prevent cracking 

let them cool on a rack outside the oven
chill in the refrigerator 
You can top your cheesecakes with your choice of jam and fruits
enjoy!

title: How to turn milk into a sweet and chewy snack in 3 minutes
description:
(â€» Resting for 30 minutes is optional. You can eat them right away without putting them in the refrigerator once the rice cakes cool down.)

I like rice cakes, so I made rice cakes with milk.
Softly melts in your mouth~
The strange taste of chewing milk :)

+ There are many people who say that the shape of rice cake is sticky.
Put the rice cakes on a plate and let it cool for a while. Then, apply sesame oil or perilla oil to the spatula to remove the stickiness.
+ The process of resting in the refrigerator for 30 minutes is to harden the rice cakes so that they are easy to eat, and has nothing to do with the process of making rice cakes.

â™£ Material
- 2T glutinous rice flour
- Starch powder 4T + 1t
- 200ml milk
- 3T sugar
- A little salt

title: Kalau kamu suka susu kamu akan senang lihat resep ini.3 bahan, no oven, murah enak.Kue Bola susu
description:
Halo semua kali ini aku bikin yang simpel dan cepat, bahannya murah cara buatnya mudah tanpa oven tapi nggak kuduga rasanya enak. 

Kue bola susu 3 bahan saja, resep asli memakai tepung tapioka ya guys dan berwarna warni, pertama lihat video 6 th lalu di channel Fun Cooking With Yackikuka, tapi kali ini aku ganti pakai tepung maizena dan ternyata juga enak. 

180 gram tepung maizena
200 gram susu kental manis
2 SDM susu bubuk

Siapkan juga 
Tepung maizena sangrai secukupnya untuk membaluri bola-bola
Susu kental manis tambahan jika adonan terlalu kering.

title: Christmas Chocolate Truffles with Milk SIMPLE Chocolate Truffle Recipe
description:
Christmas Chocolate Truffles with Milk SIMPLE Chocolate Truffle Recipe
Chocolate truffles are the best thing I know and that's why I made this video with Super delicious Chocolate Christmas Truffles. The recipe is very simple, I only used 3 ingredients for the truffle dough, Chocolate, Milk and Cocoa powder. My recipe for Christmas chocolate truffles makes 48 truffles, you can halve the recipe if you think it's a bit too many. I dip my truffles in 3 different Chocolates, but if you like a certain Chocolate best, you can dip them all in your favorite Chocolate. The decorations is very simple with dried flowers, chopped pistachio nuts and Chocolate. It's a very easy way to make Christmas goodies and really good to use for a nice little gift. Christmas Chocolate Truffles can be kept in the fridge for at least 2 weeks. Really good fun in your own kitchen making Chocolate Truffles. 
Love from Susanneâ¤ï¸ğŸ˜‰

title: Christmas PEANUT BUTTER Chocolate Truffles with Milk EASY Chocolate Truffle Recipe
description:
In this video I show the most delicious Christmas Peanut Butter Chocolate TrufflesğŸ„I have made an easy recipe with milk for Chocolate Peanut Butter Truffles. I make several different decorations in the video, e.g. one with raspberry dust and white chocolate - it immediately became one of my favourites. I also make one dipped in milk chocolate and then rolled in chopped peanuts, it's also one of the favourites. Yes, they are all delicious, they melt in your mouth. When you make Christmas Peanut Butter Chocolate Truffles and have rolled them into balls, they should not be kept in the fridge. They must be at room temperature when you dip them in Chocolate. If they are cold, they crack. The Chocolate and the oil from the Nuts seep out through the cracks. You can use Peanut Butter Truffles for small nice gifts, put them in cellophane bags with ribbons, or small sweet boxes. I'm sure those who get yours Peanut Butter Truffles will be very happyğŸ… ğŸ
I hope you want to try my Peanut Butter Chocolate Truffle Recipe at home.
Love from Susanne

title: How to make Rainbow Thousand Layer Yam Mooncake!!
description:
How to make Rainbow Thousand Layer Yam Mooncake ! 

Rainbow thousand layer Yam Mooncake

Ingredients

For Yam filling
500g Yam / Taro 
60g Caster sugar 
25g Unsalted butter 

For water dough
55g High protein flour / bread flour 
55g Low protein flour/ cake flour 
20g Icing sugar 
40g Unsalted butter 
50ml cold water
1/2 tsp lemon juice


For oil dough
100g Low protein flour/ Cake flour 
44g Clarified butter /Ghee
Food coloring
Note: 
I am making 4 colours, so each portion = 
25 g low protein flour/ cake flour  + 11 g clarified butter/ghee +1~2drops food colouring

Method
1. For filling, peel and cube the taro/yam. Steam for about 30 - 40 minutes until the taro is fork tender. Mash the taro into a paste. Mix with sugar and butter. Set aside to cool. Divide to 12 portions.
2. For water dough , mix all the ingredient and knead into a dough. Don't knead too long, as long as the ingredients are mixed nicely. Cover with cling paper and leave it to rest for about 30. 
3. For oil dough, mix 25 grams cake flour with 11 grams clarified butter /ghee, add in 1 to 2 drops food coloring. Mix everything and knead into a dough. Repeat the same step for the other 3 different colors. Wrap with cling paper and leave it aside to rest for 30 minutes.
4. Divide water dough into 6 portions. Divide the colored oil dough into 6 portion (6 portion for each color ). 
5. Roll water dough into a flat round shape, then wrap the 4 color oil dough into it. Make it into a round sphere dough. Repeat until all the dough are used up. Cover it and Leave it aside to rest for 30 minutes.
6. Shape the round sphere dough into a rectangular shape, and roll it flat as thin as possible. Do it softly and slowly and prevent it from tearing. 
7. Roll it into a log from side angle. You may choose any angle that you want, you will get different tone and different color using different angle .
8. Roll out the long log with your hands as long as possible. 
9. Using rolling spin ,roll it flat as thin as possible, remember to do it softly and slowly to prevent it from tearing .
10. Roll it up making it look like a Swiss roll. Then cut the dough into 2 pieces using a very sharp knife, do not pull or slide out the knife as it will smear the pretty colors.
11.  Slightly flatten the dough using palm . Then FLIP IT OVER making sure that the CUT side is facing DOWN.
12. Roll it flat, roughly into a size of your palm.
13. Wrap the yam filling with it , gently pull the dough upwards and around the yam filling . (Use thumb from another hand to gently apply some pressure on the filling) Seal it once the yam filling is fully covered with the dough. 
14. Bake the yam moon cake in a preheat oven at 160' C for about 20- 25 minutes. (Please observe the progress of baking as every oven differs in condition/temperature according to its quality and consistency)
15. Your beautiful Yam moon cake is now done and is ready to serve !
note: Must consume within 3 days!
